headline: How Recent Analyst Updates Are Shaping the Story Behind Prologis’s Valuation
summary: Prologis’s updated narrative reflects only a subtle lift in fair value to $131.30 and a slightly lower discount rate, as investors balance strong recent execution with more tempered long term growth assumptions. While Street research has generally moved targets higher on the back of resilient leasing demand and solid Q3 performance, some caution remains as expectations cool around how fast the top line can expand. headline: Prologis announces redemption of 3.00% Notes due 2026
summary: Prologis, Inc. (NYSE: PLD) announced today that Prologis, L.P. will redeem all of its outstanding 3.00% Notes due June 2, 2026 (CUSIP Number 74340XBB6, ISIN XS1072516690 and Common Code 107251669, the "bonds"), following which the bonds will be delisted from the New York Stock Exchange.
